02:14.760 --> 02:16.556
That's it.

02:21.157 --> 02:23.291
Forgive me God,
for I have sinned.

02:23.292 --> 02:24.759
I am king.

02:25.537 --> 02:27.962
I am king.
You have made me king.

02:28.964 --> 02:30.832
You have made me king.

02:44.180 --> 02:46.281
...forgiveness
for your sins?

02:53.889 --> 02:57.025
Do you ask God's forgiveness
for all your sins?

03:03.132 --> 03:05.567
Do you ask God's forgiveness
for all your sins?

03:07.470 --> 03:08.803
Dear God!

03:12.108 --> 03:13.475
Philip.

03:21.851 --> 03:25.086
If you wish Maud to make
your son Earl of Shiring,

03:25.087 --> 03:27.755
I need to successfully trade
Stephen with Gloucester.

03:27.756 --> 03:30.892
I'll contribute to the ransom
fee, if that's your concern.

03:30.893 --> 03:32.560
No, my concern is Stephen.

03:32.561 --> 03:35.130
If he is redeemed,
will the war continue?

03:35.131 --> 03:36.831
Undoubtedly.

03:36.832 --> 03:40.702
Therefore Queen Maud
may not rule for long,

03:40.703 --> 03:42.871
and then, whose side are we on?

03:42.872 --> 03:45.006
We need to play both sides.

03:45.007 --> 03:47.509
Oh, I intend to
do that as negotiator,

03:47.510 --> 03:51.279
but your position
is not as flexible.

03:51.280 --> 03:53.414
Are you with Maud
or are you against her?

03:53.415 --> 03:55.683
That's what Stephen will think.

03:55.684 --> 03:59.420
And as of this moment,
you are most decidedly with.

03:59.421 --> 04:00.822
Well then, if he wins,

04:00.823 --> 04:03.758
you will have to
intercede for us.

04:06.629 --> 04:09.464
You presume our position
is that of equals,

04:09.465 --> 04:12.000
I need you to serve me,
not command me.

04:19.541 --> 04:22.443
Dear Lady, you mistake
my meaning entirely.

04:22.444 --> 04:25.146
Well, then, what would
Your Eminence have me do?

04:25.147 --> 04:27.282
Whatever your wish,
I am happy to obey.

04:33.756 --> 04:36.191
I wish to be made
Archbishop of Canterbury

04:36.192 --> 04:38.026
once Stephen
regains his throne.

04:38.027 --> 04:40.995
The current one will have
to be removed, of course.

04:49.638 --> 04:51.139
Drink this, brother.

04:55.144 --> 04:56.411
How did I come here?

04:56.412 --> 04:58.713
I told the executioner that,

04:58.714 --> 04:59.914
as the Queen's secretary,

04:59.915 --> 05:01.616
I would answer for
your innocence.

05:01.617 --> 05:04.052
But I thought
you supported Stephen?

05:04.053 --> 05:05.720
Shhh!

05:05.721 --> 05:07.622
He's as self-serving
as his predecessor.

05:07.623 --> 05:10.592
I've become a
politician, Philip.

05:10.593 --> 05:12.894
I serve who best serves me.

05:14.597 --> 05:16.898
And I hear you
have a cathedral?

05:16.899 --> 05:19.100
Not yet. I need a
few miracles first.

05:19.101 --> 05:21.202
Then let us
give thanks, brother.

05:21.203 --> 05:23.571
This is a day for miracles.

05:23.572 --> 05:26.207
I found you,
Maud is now in power.

05:26.208 --> 05:30.445
And the dead have
returned to life.

05:30.446 --> 05:35.250
They found him crawling
from a mass grave.

05:44.460 --> 05:46.527
You're a new man, Jack.

05:46.528 --> 05:48.062
A Lazarus.

05:49.531 --> 05:51.599
I'm sure I stink like Lazarus.

05:53.669 --> 05:56.271
You must have died too,
from the look of you.

05:56.272 --> 05:58.006
Nearly.

05:58.007 --> 06:00.508
God has further plans for me.
For you too, I suspect.

06:00.509 --> 06:02.243
What plans?

06:05.581 --> 06:07.782
What do you remember
of the last 3 days?

06:07.783 --> 06:09.250
Did you pray?

06:09.251 --> 06:11.386
I was laying with the dead.

06:12.855 --> 06:15.256
I suppose I don't remember.

06:17.593 --> 06:19.661
I dreamt, though.
I remember that.

06:19.662 --> 06:21.162
What of?

06:22.598 --> 06:24.198
Of Aliena.

06:55.230 --> 06:56.364
Lovely evening.

06:56.365 --> 06:57.832
What are you doing here?

06:57.833 --> 07:00.601
I just came out
to look at the moon.

07:00.602 --> 07:02.970
No. No, wait!

07:02.971 --> 07:05.973
Aliena, don't go.
I can't swim very well!

07:05.974 --> 07:07.041
Help!

07:07.042 --> 07:08.876
Aliena! Help!

07:16.051 --> 07:17.919
Alfred?

07:39.608 --> 07:41.376
Don't come near me again.

07:42.678 --> 07:43.711
What?

07:48.050 --> 07:49.851
But I love you!

07:51.887 --> 07:53.688
I love you!

08:02.531 --> 08:05.299
- The Empress's terms
are non-negotiable.

08:05.300 --> 08:08.236
Stephen must sign a document
acknowledging her sovereignty

08:08.237 --> 08:10.204
and leave the country forever.

08:10.205 --> 08:13.074
In addition, you will pay Maud
1,000 pounds in gold

08:13.075 --> 08:15.910
and hand over Robert of
Gloucester in good health.

08:17.346 --> 08:19.080
Interesting.

08:19.081 --> 08:21.749
We were gonna ask
1,000 pounds from you.

08:23.051 --> 08:25.987
Why not cancel the ransom fees
and proceed from there?

08:25.988 --> 08:28.289
Your Eminence,
may I have a word?

08:29.792 --> 08:31.359
We need the fee

08:31.360 --> 08:32.960
in order to bankrupt them.

08:32.961 --> 08:35.395
Otherwise, what guarantee
do we have

08:35.397 --> 08:38.533
that Stephen won't ignore
anything that he signs

08:38.534 --> 08:40.534
and begin a war again?

08:40.535 --> 08:43.371
We need a guarantee.

08:44.740 --> 08:47.008
If we ignore the ransom fees,

08:48.010 --> 08:51.245
we need to hold
Stephen's son, Eustace,

08:51.246 --> 08:53.114
until his father
has left the country

08:53.115 --> 08:55.016
and peace has been kept
for 5 years.

08:55.017 --> 08:56.584
King Stephen will never agree.

08:56.585 --> 08:58.085
It's not his decision.

09:01.423 --> 09:04.759
Think about it overnight...

09:04.760 --> 09:06.994
dear Richard.

09:11.066 --> 09:13.434
No one at Maud's court

09:13.435 --> 09:15.369
knows what Eustace
looks like, do they?

09:35.724 --> 09:37.358
And what's your name?

09:37.359 --> 09:38.559
Elizabeth.

09:38.560 --> 09:41.128
That's a pretty name.
How old are you, Elizabeth?

09:41.129 --> 09:42.230
I'm 12.

09:43.298 --> 09:44.999
You're a very pretty girl...

09:45.000 --> 09:47.335
with very pretty lips.

09:47.336 --> 09:48.970
Has anyone ever told you that?

10:02.518 --> 10:04.418
Good day, Bishop.

10:08.657 --> 10:11.058
I thought you were for Stephen.

10:31.213 --> 10:33.481
Do you see these people
before us, Henry?

10:33.482 --> 10:34.849
Yes, Mama.

10:34.850 --> 10:37.818
They've come to ask us favors.
Do you know why?

10:37.819 --> 10:38.920
You're the Queen.

10:38.921 --> 10:40.588
I'm the Empress.

10:40.589 --> 10:43.090
I rechristened myself
this morning.

10:43.091 --> 10:46.027
And one day,
you will be Emperor,

10:46.028 --> 10:48.462
and people will come
to ask you favors.

10:48.463 --> 10:50.598
So I want you to listen.

10:50.599 --> 10:53.834
Francis, you may speak first.

10:53.835 --> 10:57.271
And who is this handsome man?

10:57.272 --> 11:00.241
This is my brother,
Philip, Empress,

11:00.242 --> 11:02.176
the Prior of Kingsbridge.

11:02.177 --> 11:04.378
Handsome, I pray,
before God, Empress,

11:04.379 --> 11:07.014
but, uh, very plain to others.

11:07.015 --> 11:10.851
Humility and humor,
a rare combination.

11:10.852 --> 11:14.488
You ask us to grant you
a license to hold a market?

11:14.489 --> 11:16.490
The income from which
will be used

11:16.491 --> 11:18.292
to finish building a cathedral.

11:18.293 --> 11:20.094
Finish? How did you pay
to start it?

11:20.095 --> 11:22.563
We had a license, Empress,
but it was lost.

11:22.564 --> 11:25.232
King Steph...
Uh, the usurper Stephen refused

11:25.233 --> 11:26.534
to grant us an other.

11:26.535 --> 11:27.602
Why is that?

11:27.603 --> 11:30.071
He kept his reasons to himself.

11:30.072 --> 11:32.506
May I speak, My Empress?

11:32.507 --> 11:35.343
The market at Kingsbridge
was closed,

11:35.344 --> 11:37.812
because it took money
from the one at Shiring.

11:37.813 --> 11:41.282
The rule is that markets must
be at least 14 miles apart.

11:41.283 --> 11:43.451
Kingsbridge and Shiring are 20.

11:43.452 --> 11:45.853
Stephen nevertheless decided...

11:45.854 --> 11:48.756
What Stephen decided
is of no interest to us.

11:48.757 --> 11:51.726
You also ask the right to take
stone from the Shiring quarry.

11:51.727 --> 11:54.662
We have had those rights
for years until William...

11:54.663 --> 11:58.099
I closed the quarry
in retaliation

11:58.100 --> 11:59.667
for his illegal market.

11:59.668 --> 12:01.402
Who owns the quarry?

12:01.403 --> 12:02.436
We do, My Empress,

12:02.437 --> 12:03.838
It was the usurper Stephen

12:03.839 --> 12:06.140
that allowed Kingsbridge
to take the stones.

12:06.141 --> 12:09.443
A foolish bequest, giving
quarry rights to one party,

12:09.444 --> 12:11.178
yet letting another mine it.

12:11.179 --> 12:13.414
We quite agree.

12:13.415 --> 12:16.584
The quarry and all its mining
rights shall belong to Shiring.

12:16.585 --> 12:18.119
Thank you, My Empress.

12:18.120 --> 12:20.688
On the condition that you
successfully negotiate

12:20.689 --> 12:23.457
the release of
our brother Gloucester

12:23.458 --> 12:25.826
from the enemy.

12:25.827 --> 12:28.729
Kingsbridge, however,
shall have similar market rights

12:28.730 --> 12:30.531
to Shiring.

12:30.532 --> 12:32.166
The same condition applies.

12:32.167 --> 12:33.934
Thank you, Empress.

12:40.976 --> 12:45.346
In addition, Henry here would
like a toy from each of you.

12:47.482 --> 12:48.783
And I'd like a toy, too.

12:48.784 --> 12:52.987
100 pounds or your requests
will be denied.

12:52.988 --> 12:54.855
Next.

12:57.125 --> 12:58.292
Can you borrow it?

12:58.293 --> 13:00.261
Money lenders charge
exorbitant interest.

13:00.262 --> 13:01.462
I could never pay it back.

13:01.463 --> 13:02.730
No one else?

13:02.731 --> 13:04.465
A merchant who benefits
from the market?

13:04.466 --> 13:06.100
He might find it
to his advantage.

13:06.101 --> 13:07.134
- She.
- What?

13:07.135 --> 13:08.502
She.

13:09.504 --> 13:11.405
I did her a favor once.

13:13.942 --> 13:15.643
We've just received the word!

13:15.644 --> 13:17.044
What? Martha,
what is it?

13:17.045 --> 13:18.646
Jack's alive!

13:27.522 --> 13:29.056
- What? Martha,
- Jack, Jack, Jack! is it?

13:30.992 --> 13:32.626
Hey, Jack!

13:32.694 --> 13:34.662
Jack!

13:36.131 --> 13:38.265
Jack!

13:39.868 --> 13:41.569
Brother, welcome home.

13:41.636 --> 13:43.504
Welcome home!

13:43.572 --> 13:45.239
Welcome back, Jack!

13:46.508 --> 13:48.275
Good to see you, man!

13:50.979 --> 13:52.947
Prior Philip is back.

14:21.276 --> 14:23.811
100 pounds?
I'd lend it to you gladly,

14:23.812 --> 14:26.881
but I need it to buy
next's year's wool.

14:26.882 --> 14:28.649
When would you
need it returned?

14:28.650 --> 14:30.351
Early spring.
Can you manage it?

14:30.352 --> 14:31.685
No.

14:31.686 --> 14:32.887
No, not unless...

14:32.888 --> 14:34.889
Why can't I sell you
next year's wool?

14:34.890 --> 14:37.758
- You haven't got it yet.
- I will in the spring.

14:37.759 --> 14:39.260
You'd sell it in advance?

14:39.261 --> 14:41.495
Pay me now and I give you
the first shearing.

14:41.496 --> 14:43.330
I never heard of
it done like that.

14:43.331 --> 14:44.398
Why shouldn't it be?

14:44.399 --> 14:45.733
I'd have to offer you

14:45.734 --> 14:46.867
a lower price for it

14:46.868 --> 14:48.369
than you'd get by waiting.

14:48.370 --> 14:50.371
The price for wool
goes up in the spring.

14:50.372 --> 14:52.039
I could keep building in winter

14:52.040 --> 14:53.741
and everybody
would be employed.

14:53.742 --> 14:56.210
So I give you 100 pounds,
you give it to Maud

14:56.211 --> 14:57.378
and you get a license?

14:57.379 --> 14:58.579
The same as Shiring.

14:58.580 --> 15:00.080
In addition to
the Sunday market,

15:00.081 --> 15:01.916
Shiring has the
annual fleece fair.

15:01.917 --> 15:04.051
That's where I make
most of my money.

15:04.052 --> 15:06.053
I... I don't follow.

15:06.054 --> 15:07.655
Why don't we have one here?

15:07.656 --> 15:10.224
If the license is
the same as Shiring's,

15:10.225 --> 15:13.360
why can't you host a fair next
year to compete with Shiring?

15:13.361 --> 15:14.995
It would save me
transportation.

15:14.996 --> 15:16.931
I could lure
the Flemish buyers here.

15:16.932 --> 15:19.033
You would make
more money in a week

15:19.034 --> 15:21.202
than you would in
a year of Sunday markets

15:21.203 --> 15:23.470
and it would break
the Hamleighs' back.

15:23.471 --> 15:25.072
Ha! Brilliant!

15:25.073 --> 15:27.708
William would be
as mad as a bull!

15:27.709 --> 15:30.010
Yes, and there's nothing
he can do about it.

15:36.218 --> 15:38.419
♪ ♪ ♪

15:39.788 --> 15:41.155
Welcome back.

15:45.994 --> 15:47.361
Thank you.

16:47.355 --> 16:49.123
I knew you weren't dead.

16:49.124 --> 16:51.392
You shouldn't be here.
They'll see you.

16:51.393 --> 16:53.560
No. Even Waleran
can't keep me from my son.

17:05.540 --> 17:07.540
Come on!
What are you doing?

17:08.910 --> 17:10.344
I'm trying to be helpful!

17:29.531 --> 17:30.531
Ow!

18:30.058 --> 18:32.526
Walter will take the boy.

18:49.110 --> 18:51.111
Who is that boy you gave them?

18:51.112 --> 18:52.846
Your son Eustace, Sire.

18:52.847 --> 18:54.615
That wasn't Eustace.

18:54.616 --> 18:56.417
Well, they don't know that.

18:58.853 --> 19:00.754
Brother.

19:00.755 --> 19:02.322
My dear Maud.

19:05.727 --> 19:08.962
So, war begins again.

19:08.963 --> 19:10.964
And chaos is king.

19:10.965 --> 19:13.100
I don't see how
that benefits us.

19:13.101 --> 19:15.369
Oh, when chaos
reigns, dear Lady,

19:15.370 --> 19:18.572
Satan often forgets about
God's humble servants,

19:18.573 --> 19:21.708
and we may carry on with our
holy work without interference.

19:21.709 --> 19:23.010
Attack!

19:31.953 --> 19:34.188
Yah! Yah!

19:38.693 --> 19:40.027
We are betrayed!

19:40.028 --> 19:41.762
Stephen has attacked
us once again!

19:41.763 --> 19:43.997
Does he honestly think
we'll spare his son?

19:43.998 --> 19:46.600
Empress, I fear,
sadly, the boy is...

19:47.602 --> 19:48.769
is not his.

19:48.770 --> 19:50.437
He says his name is Charlie

19:50.438 --> 19:52.005
and he's missing his pigs.

19:52.006 --> 19:55.175
Richard of Kingsbridge
substituted a farmer's child

19:55.176 --> 19:56.677
for Eustace.

19:56.678 --> 19:59.113
He resembles the
usurper's son near enough.

19:59.114 --> 20:00.781
He even fooled me, Empress.

20:02.117 --> 20:04.251
Kill him anyway.

20:04.252 --> 20:07.855
Stephen will learn
that we, at least,

20:07.856 --> 20:09.790
keep our promises

20:09.791 --> 20:12.993
and we are not to be crossed!

21:24.866 --> 21:27.935
<i>Dear sister,
once again we're at war.</i>

21:27.936 --> 21:30.337
Advance is slow but sure.

21:30.338 --> 21:34.174
<i>And we hope by spring
to defeat Maud and Gloucester.</i>

21:34.175 --> 21:37.611
Of course, since I fight
for Stephen, if Maud wins,

21:37.612 --> 21:41.248
<i>I might never regain Shiring
and Father's title.</i>

21:42.650 --> 21:45.152
<i>William and is mother have
taken Maud's side,</i>

21:45.153 --> 21:46.486
<i>for the time being,</i>

21:46.487 --> 21:49.156
<i>but their loyalty is
as dependable as snow</i>

21:49.157 --> 21:51.758
<i>and goes wherever
the winds of power blow it.</i>

21:51.759 --> 21:55.362
Their ally, Bishop Waleran,
has already laid the groundwork

21:55.363 --> 21:58.532
<i>for siding again with Stephen
if he were to win.</i>

21:58.533 --> 22:00.534
You must forgive my despair.

22:00.535 --> 22:03.837
Winter slows the war and gives
me too much time to brood.

22:03.838 --> 22:07.274
<i>It has stopped
cathedral work too, I imagine.</i>

22:08.610 --> 22:10.010
<i>But come spring,</i>

22:10.011 --> 22:12.312
<i>Hope may blossom,
the war may end,</i>

22:12.313 --> 22:15.415
<i>the church walls
may rise ever higher,</i>

22:15.416 --> 22:18.986
<i>and I will once again
return to your dear self.</i>

22:18.987 --> 22:21.321
<i>Until then,</i>

22:21.322 --> 22:25.025
<i>I remain your
loving brother, Richard.</i>

22:30.798 --> 22:34.134
One, two, three!

22:35.336 --> 22:37.004
You started work late today.

22:38.606 --> 22:40.073
Late?

22:40.074 --> 22:43.043
Well, there's not much we can do
without a stock of stones.

22:43.044 --> 22:45.912
Nevertheless, I thought it
would be further along by now.

22:45.913 --> 22:47.948
We can't work
in the winter, Prior.

22:47.949 --> 22:49.983
And when we get more stones...

22:49.984 --> 22:51.685
And if we don't?

22:51.686 --> 22:54.488
You should've conserved
their use, Tom.

22:54.489 --> 22:57.324
Jack's been using too many,
carving gargoyles.

22:58.593 --> 23:01.028
Well, we can purchase
some more soon.

23:01.029 --> 23:02.729
You paid your debt to Maud,

23:02.730 --> 23:04.564
She's given you
a license for a market.

23:04.565 --> 23:06.933
Maud is losing battle
after battle.

23:06.934 --> 23:09.703
What happens to my fee
if she's deposed?

23:09.704 --> 23:12.873
They'll be no more stones
and the coffers will be empty.

23:12.874 --> 23:14.741
Get off there. Get off!

23:14.742 --> 23:16.777
Steady hands!
Keep it level.

23:18.546 --> 23:20.614
Da, look!

23:20.615 --> 23:22.816
If I can do this,
I can build a stone vault.

23:22.817 --> 23:24.618
How many times
do I have to tell you?

23:24.619 --> 23:27.754
A stone vault is too heavy.
It can't be supported.

23:27.755 --> 23:28.889
Why don't you listen?

23:38.366 --> 23:40.467
How many of these
have you made?

23:40.468 --> 23:41.735
Sixteen, so far.

23:41.736 --> 23:44.571
It's a little bit of fun
in God's house.

23:45.907 --> 23:48.208
What a waste.

23:50.778 --> 23:52.779
♪ ♪ ♪

23:52.780 --> 23:54.648
Philip's in a sour mood.

23:54.649 --> 23:57.951
All employers get like this
at some point.

23:57.952 --> 23:59.986
See, the work starts
to slow down,

23:59.987 --> 24:02.055
it costs more than
they ever imagined,

24:02.056 --> 24:05.392
and all they can think
to do is complain.

24:05.393 --> 24:08.729
They can't see the future,
which, as a builder, I have to.

24:08.730 --> 24:10.964
As a cathedral
builder especially.

24:10.965 --> 24:13.066
No pessimists allowed.

24:15.570 --> 24:17.170
But realists, yes.

24:19.107 --> 24:21.541
I won't see
this church completed.

24:22.977 --> 24:24.578
Da?

24:24.579 --> 24:26.046
Nor will you, Alfred.

24:26.047 --> 24:28.081
Nor you, Jack, most likely.

24:29.183 --> 24:31.852
I may see it roofed.

24:31.853 --> 24:34.588
You might see the interior
well on its way.

24:35.890 --> 24:38.992
But it might be 50 years
before it's finished,

24:38.993 --> 24:40.394
which is why I teach you.

24:40.395 --> 24:42.929
That's why you must
never stop learning...

24:44.599 --> 24:46.466
even after I'm gone.

24:48.102 --> 24:49.569
Learn from who?

24:49.570 --> 24:51.171
From your pupils.

24:51.172 --> 24:54.875
Your younger masters, they might
find new ways to perfection.

24:56.911 --> 24:59.146
Do you know what this is?

24:59.147 --> 25:00.781
That's glass.

25:00.782 --> 25:03.250
What if I were
to tell you that one day,

25:03.251 --> 25:06.052
this is what cathedrals
will be built from?

25:06.053 --> 25:07.521
Ha! Never.

25:07.522 --> 25:10.791
"Never" is a word
you must never use.

25:16.030 --> 25:18.365
Now, this is all I have,

25:18.366 --> 25:19.766
right here,

25:19.767 --> 25:22.102
to pass on to my successor.

25:22.103 --> 25:23.904
You're both my sons,

25:23.905 --> 25:27.374
Now, I'd like to be able
to share ownership

25:27.375 --> 25:30.110
between the two of you,
but I know that

25:30.111 --> 25:32.779
sometimes you work
at cross purposes.

25:32.780 --> 25:35.782
I'd really like it if you could
try your best to be friends.

25:38.119 --> 25:39.653
And if not,

25:39.654 --> 25:41.955
the one that gets this

25:41.956 --> 25:45.992
will be the one that best
embodies my vision, my knowledge

25:45.993 --> 25:47.494
and my belief in the future.

25:51.532 --> 25:53.633
Do you understand that?

25:58.239 --> 25:59.372
Bastard!

25:59.373 --> 26:01.441
Jack, you bastard,

26:01.442 --> 26:03.510
you are not my brother!

26:37.845 --> 26:39.279
Marry me.

26:41.616 --> 26:43.183
Marry me.

26:44.952 --> 26:46.386
No.

27:03.070 --> 27:04.905
- Morning.
- Oh!

27:06.974 --> 27:09.809
Oh God!
Don't ever sneak up on me.

27:09.810 --> 27:12.012
I didn't.
I made a lot of noise.

27:12.013 --> 27:15.549
You were just so engrossed in
that, that you didn't hear me.

27:15.550 --> 27:18.184
I've never heard of
a woman with such a library.

27:19.186 --> 27:21.021
Which one is this?

27:31.899 --> 27:33.066
The Song of Roland.

27:33.067 --> 27:35.835
It's about this knight
who has a big horn.

27:35.836 --> 27:37.037
He blows it so hard...

27:37.038 --> 27:39.439
That his head bursts.

27:39.440 --> 27:40.640
You know it?

27:40.641 --> 27:42.742
My mother told it to me
when I was a boy.

27:42.743 --> 27:44.477
But she didn't call him Roland.

27:44.478 --> 27:46.680
She changed the name
to Foolish Jack.

27:46.681 --> 27:48.148
How would she heard of it?

27:48.149 --> 27:50.116
My father told it to her.

27:50.117 --> 27:53.219
"The French seduction"
is how she described it.

27:53.220 --> 27:54.754
He was French?

27:54.755 --> 27:56.389
He was a story teller.

27:56.390 --> 27:59.593
In fact, apparently she laughed
so hard at that one,

27:59.594 --> 28:00.860
that he got very angry.

28:02.129 --> 28:03.930
Did she know any others?

28:03.931 --> 28:05.365
Yeah, a few.

28:05.366 --> 28:07.968
But the best were
the ones that I told her.

28:09.203 --> 28:10.470
You?

28:10.471 --> 28:12.906
Yeah, I made them up, you know.

28:12.907 --> 28:14.808
There once...

28:16.243 --> 28:18.578
There once was
a very brave knight.

28:18.579 --> 28:20.280
Who...

28:20.281 --> 28:22.482
Who...

28:22.483 --> 28:24.117
Who went into battle

28:25.119 --> 28:28.021
and received a mortal wound.

28:28.022 --> 28:30.023
And as he lay there, dying,

28:30.024 --> 28:32.125
his soul...

28:32.126 --> 28:35.061
Flew to the house
where there lived a woman...

28:35.062 --> 28:36.029
That he loved.

28:36.030 --> 28:37.063
Yes.

28:37.064 --> 28:38.431
And his...

28:38.432 --> 28:40.233
His soul ate with her

28:40.234 --> 28:42.769
and slept with her

28:42.770 --> 28:46.139
and was so filled
with longing for her...

28:47.441 --> 28:49.175
He flew back to his master

28:49.176 --> 28:50.877
and brought him back to life.

28:51.879 --> 28:53.613
In hope that one day...

29:11.599 --> 29:13.566
No!

29:15.436 --> 29:16.569
All right?

29:16.570 --> 29:18.038
Don't touch me there.

29:18.039 --> 29:19.739
Don't you ever touch me again!

29:25.846 --> 29:27.847
Jack! Jack!

29:27.848 --> 29:29.249
Come quick!

29:35.790 --> 29:38.158
It's Alfred! He smashed
all of your statues.

29:38.159 --> 29:39.426
What?

29:39.427 --> 29:40.827
He smashed them all.

30:06.921 --> 30:09.489
Come on, boys!
Help me!

30:09.490 --> 30:12.025
There's fighting.

30:35.182 --> 30:38.985
The scaffolding is
not made for that violence!

31:10.151 --> 31:11.718
It's not the first time, Tom.

31:11.719 --> 31:12.986
But Philip, what bro...

31:12.987 --> 31:14.220
No! No excuses.

31:14.221 --> 31:16.356
If 2 of your workers
continually fight,

31:16.357 --> 31:17.824
destroy property,

31:17.825 --> 31:20.660
tear down work that you
spent months building up,

31:20.661 --> 31:22.095
what do you do?

31:24.832 --> 31:28.201
I will not have Jack and
Alfred working together.

31:28.202 --> 31:29.836
Look...

31:29.837 --> 31:31.237
One of them must go.

31:32.273 --> 31:33.740
He's an apprentice!

31:33.741 --> 31:35.308
I'm a master stonemason,

31:35.309 --> 31:37.210
Send him away, Da, not me.

31:37.211 --> 31:39.412
I'm your real son!

31:39.413 --> 31:42.749
If Ma was alive, this wouldn't
even be a choice!

31:42.750 --> 31:45.552
We were a team once, remember?

31:45.553 --> 31:48.021
I was supposed to
be your successor.

31:48.022 --> 31:51.457
Alfred, you'll have to pay
a fine for the damage caused.

31:51.458 --> 31:52.892
One month's wages.
A month?

31:52.893 --> 31:55.061
Doubt the prior
would accept any less.

31:55.062 --> 31:57.197
Leave us for a moment.

31:57.198 --> 31:58.198
Da!

31:58.199 --> 32:00.066
Go... before
I double it.

32:07.174 --> 32:08.708
That one over here?

32:10.611 --> 32:12.011
I'm sorry, Jack.

32:12.012 --> 32:14.047
Why me?

32:14.048 --> 32:16.282
I pleaded with Philip,
but he wouldn't soften.

32:16.283 --> 32:18.251
This is my life.

32:19.320 --> 32:20.954
He's my son.

32:20.955 --> 32:22.555
I'm your son too.
You said it.

32:26.393 --> 32:29.529
You're the one
that Philip will miss.

32:29.530 --> 32:30.964
You know, Alfred...

32:32.600 --> 32:34.667
he's competent.

32:38.005 --> 32:39.505
But you're brilliant.

32:41.408 --> 32:43.209
Now, in a week or a month,

32:43.210 --> 32:45.411
the Prior will see his mistake.

32:45.412 --> 32:46.846
And if he doesn't?

32:48.782 --> 32:52.318
You wouldn't even have a job
if it weren't for me.

32:52.319 --> 32:53.620
That's enough.

32:53.621 --> 32:56.222
Do you hear what I'm saying?
I burned it down.

32:56.223 --> 32:59.926
I burned the old cathedral
so that you would have work.

33:11.805 --> 33:13.706
God forgive you then.

33:15.809 --> 33:17.644
Get out.

33:19.813 --> 33:22.015
Get out!

33:45.205 --> 33:47.106
Can I climb it?

33:53.147 --> 33:57.083
What do you wanna climb all
the way up there for, Jonathan?

33:57.084 --> 33:58.184
Brother Jonathan.

33:58.185 --> 33:59.953
Brother Jonathan.

33:59.954 --> 34:01.354
So I can see Jack.

34:01.355 --> 34:03.489
He's gone away and
he hasn't said good-bye.

34:06.994 --> 34:08.261
Sit down.

34:20.808 --> 34:23.943
Jack went away because
he'd done something bad.

34:26.981 --> 34:28.514
He hurt Alfred.

34:28.514 --> 34:30.116
Like Cain hurt Abel?

34:30.117 --> 34:32.452
No, not as bad as that,

34:32.453 --> 34:35.722
but anyway. Jack and Alfred
are not really brothers.

34:35.723 --> 34:37.422
Isn't Jack your son?

34:37.424 --> 34:40.693
Well, I'm raising...
was raising... Jack

34:40.694 --> 34:41.995
as a favor to Ellen,

34:43.030 --> 34:44.864
like Johnny Eightpence
raises you.

34:44.864 --> 34:47.967
He isn't my mother,
but he likes to think he is.

34:47.967 --> 34:49.268
I know.

34:49.268 --> 34:51.170
My mother's dead.

34:53.239 --> 34:55.641
I know that.

34:55.641 --> 34:58.011
That's all of them.
Take them away now.

34:58.012 --> 35:00.246
Do you know who my father is?

35:03.117 --> 35:04.550
Who?

35:04.551 --> 35:06.719
God.
He's everybody's father.

35:08.789 --> 35:10.490
Of course he is.

35:18.732 --> 35:20.066
Where will you go?

35:20.067 --> 35:22.135
Wherever they're
building cathedrals,

35:22.136 --> 35:24.037
I'll go to Jerusalem
if I have to.

35:24.038 --> 35:25.171
Philip is wrong.

35:25.172 --> 35:27.140
He will understand that
he made a mistake.

35:27.141 --> 35:30.009
Philip's stubborn, you push
against him and he pushes back.

35:30.010 --> 35:32.145
It would take witchcraft
to change his mind.

35:44.992 --> 35:46.793
Come in, Tom.

35:51.198 --> 35:53.066
What are you doing here?

35:53.067 --> 35:55.034
You saved my life, once.

35:55.035 --> 35:56.469
I know you're a man of mercy.

35:56.470 --> 35:58.504
How did you get inside?

35:58.505 --> 36:01.140
Not all of the brothers
fear me as you do.

36:01.141 --> 36:03.009
- Ma.
- Let me speak, Jack.

36:10.017 --> 36:11.617
I don't fear you.

36:11.618 --> 36:13.419
I oppose what you stand for,

36:13.420 --> 36:16.622
which is hatred of God,
and church and morality.

36:18.892 --> 36:20.393
I love God.

36:20.394 --> 36:23.830
Although I don't worship Her
quite the same way as you do.

36:23.831 --> 36:26.599
My church hasn't
as many rules as yours

36:26.600 --> 36:28.568
and is a lot more forgiving.

36:28.569 --> 36:31.170
And as for morality,
I use love as my compass,

36:31.171 --> 36:34.207
which Christ seemed
to approve of,

36:34.208 --> 36:35.808
even if you don't.

36:35.809 --> 36:37.310
Ma, you promised to be civil.

36:43.183 --> 36:45.318
Come in.
Close the door.

36:53.260 --> 36:56.696
I spend too much time making
decisions on the building.

36:56.697 --> 36:58.397
I need an assistant

36:58.398 --> 37:00.333
who can answer queries
on construction,

37:00.334 --> 37:02.869
who can keep track of
the money and raw materials,

37:02.870 --> 37:05.705
who can handle payments to
suppliers, who can pay wages.

37:05.706 --> 37:07.206
You wouldn't be carving stone,

37:07.207 --> 37:10.476
but you would be supervising
the entire design on my behalf.

37:10.477 --> 37:11.744
Really?

37:16.650 --> 37:17.984
Prior, that's fantastic.

37:17.985 --> 37:20.686
In your spare time,
if you had any,

37:20.687 --> 37:22.622
you'd learn speak
and read Latin.

37:22.623 --> 37:24.056
You'd serve me during Mass...

37:24.057 --> 37:26.192
Why would he need to do that?

37:26.193 --> 37:28.060
Because my assistant
must be a monk.

37:28.061 --> 37:29.795
Your church is not
having my son.

37:29.796 --> 37:32.198
That's Jack's
decision, not yours.

37:32.199 --> 37:33.466
It burned his father.

37:33.467 --> 37:35.501
It tried to burn me.
Ma!

37:37.838 --> 37:39.839
If I found the time,

37:40.941 --> 37:42.675
could I do some carving?

37:43.677 --> 37:46.078
Yes, of course.

37:46.079 --> 37:48.881
And I'll have free reign
to walk the grounds,

37:48.882 --> 37:50.249
speak with whomever I wish?

37:50.250 --> 37:52.485
You may speak to men,
on business, yes.

37:55.689 --> 37:57.657
God wants you, Jack.

37:57.658 --> 37:59.992
Of that I'm certain.

38:01.295 --> 38:03.229
He saved your life.

38:04.932 --> 38:06.599
He speaks to you
through your art

38:06.600 --> 38:09.502
as clearly as he spoke
to Augustine, Gregory,

38:09.503 --> 38:10.836
all His artist-saints.

38:10.837 --> 38:14.106
Do you want God?

38:17.911 --> 38:19.679
It's a simple choice...

38:20.747 --> 38:22.081
not an easy one.

38:56.350 --> 38:57.783
Rise.

39:21.375 --> 39:23.009
Put your hood on.

39:37.291 --> 39:39.625
Kingsbridge is planning
a fleece fair

39:39.626 --> 39:42.161
and Shiring shall become
a village of ghosts!

39:42.162 --> 39:43.763
Who told you this?

39:43.764 --> 39:47.033
Two of the Flemish traders who
normally do business with us.

39:47.034 --> 39:49.735
It's planned for
the last Sunday in June.

39:49.736 --> 39:51.504
That's 2 weeks from now.

39:51.505 --> 39:52.905
How can we stop it?

39:55.142 --> 39:58.411
That is a lovely stone.

40:01.982 --> 40:03.382
No.

40:03.383 --> 40:04.817
This belonged to my father.

40:04.818 --> 40:07.153
It's all I've got left of him.

40:07.154 --> 40:09.388
Queen Maud, as you well know,

40:09.389 --> 40:11.223
is fleeing back to France.

40:11.224 --> 40:13.959
Stephen thinks you are
both traitors.

40:13.960 --> 40:16.429
How else will I
convince him you're not?

40:16.430 --> 40:17.430
He loves a gift.

40:20.600 --> 40:23.536
Get him to stop the fair.

40:23.537 --> 40:26.639
Dear Lady, the fair
will begin, as planned,

40:26.640 --> 40:29.342
but it will not end as planned,

40:29.343 --> 40:31.377
will it, William?

40:37.818 --> 40:39.819
Don't be nervous, My Lord.

40:41.088 --> 40:43.022
Take your lesson

40:43.023 --> 40:45.991
Some take it as a work of art,

40:45.992 --> 40:47.760
a reason for living.

40:47.761 --> 40:52.231
Well, I say destruction
is a work of art...

40:54.034 --> 40:56.602
...and requires
significant talent.

40:58.972 --> 41:01.307
You have a gift, Lord William.

41:03.243 --> 41:05.578
Let's make your mother proud.

41:15.222 --> 41:16.889
♪ ♪ ♪

41:19.025 --> 41:22.328
You couldn't ask for
a better crowd,

41:22.329 --> 41:23.396
could you, Father?

41:23.397 --> 41:24.630
Or better weather.

41:24.631 --> 41:27.233
God's been good to us, today.

41:30.237 --> 41:31.504
Entrance.

41:32.506 --> 41:34.407
Entrance fee.

41:38.412 --> 41:39.879
Hello, brother dear.

41:39.880 --> 41:41.781
Kate!
Ah, Kate!

41:43.049 --> 41:44.450
Have you...

41:44.451 --> 41:46.152
Have you come to be shriven?

41:46.153 --> 41:48.921
Oh sweet Jesus!
I've prayed for this every day.

41:48.922 --> 41:52.191
I came to sell
my wares, Cuthbert.

41:52.192 --> 41:54.427
Any of your monks
interested in buying?

41:55.929 --> 41:58.197
Oh, that place.
In the shade.

41:58.198 --> 41:59.698
OK.
In the tree.

42:00.867 --> 42:02.935
Did I, uh...

42:02.936 --> 42:04.904
did I see Ellen here?

42:06.139 --> 42:08.207
Yes, she came to see her son.

42:09.242 --> 42:10.476
Not me.

42:10.477 --> 42:12.211
She's still angry with me

42:12.212 --> 42:14.447
for going along with your idea.

42:14.448 --> 42:17.450
She's a good woman, Prior.
You should accept her as she is.

42:17.451 --> 42:19.652
You're not gonna be able
to convert everyone.

42:19.653 --> 42:21.320
But I can bring her son to God.

42:21.321 --> 42:23.522
He's doing wonderful work.

42:23.523 --> 42:24.924
You should tell her that.

42:24.925 --> 42:28.427
If the Good Lord Himself came
down from heaven to praise him,

42:28.428 --> 42:30.696
I don't think that would
make her happy.

42:32.265 --> 42:34.300
40,000 sheep sold me
their winter coats.

42:34.301 --> 42:36.302
Would you believe it?

42:36.303 --> 42:37.770
It's cost me 200 pounds,

42:37.771 --> 42:39.305
but I'll make 3.

42:39.306 --> 42:42.041
Even I lose my breath
when I think about it.

42:42.042 --> 42:43.476
If you need help,

42:43.477 --> 42:46.545
I will gladly stick around
after I see Jack.

42:46.546 --> 42:49.114
Ellen, I know how hard
it must've been for you.

42:49.115 --> 42:52.451
I'm perfectly fine. It's Jack
you should worry about.

42:52.452 --> 42:54.420
He seems happy.

42:54.421 --> 42:57.623
Good. That's all
a mother asks for.

42:57.624 --> 42:59.325
What is?

43:00.627 --> 43:02.895
Oh I don't look that bad, do I?

43:02.896 --> 43:04.964
You've lost weight.
They're starving you.

43:04.965 --> 43:07.299
They feed me too well, Ma.

43:07.300 --> 43:08.467
You look exhausted.

43:08.468 --> 43:10.336
How many minutes of sleep

43:10.337 --> 43:11.904
do they allow you
between prayers?

43:11.905 --> 43:14.073
Oh I skip most of
the services, so...

43:14.074 --> 43:16.008
Do the monks try
to sleep with you?

43:16.009 --> 43:17.743
Ma...

43:17.744 --> 43:20.246
No, I have no interest
along those lines

43:20.247 --> 43:22.481
and even if I did,
it's forbidden.

43:22.482 --> 43:24.650
Do you have interest
along other lines?

43:24.651 --> 43:27.286
- What?
- Do you pleasure yourself?

43:27.287 --> 43:28.988
Ma!

43:28.989 --> 43:31.524
I... No!
I don't, no.

43:33.793 --> 43:35.528
That's unnatural.

43:40.734 --> 43:43.702
I want to make
a confession, Father.

43:43.703 --> 43:45.638
Mmm...

43:51.611 --> 43:53.145
You're Kate, aren't you?

43:53.146 --> 43:55.347
Brother Cuthbert's
little sister.

43:55.348 --> 43:56.515
I remember you well.

43:56.516 --> 43:57.716
What's it to you?

43:57.717 --> 43:59.318
You're everything to him.

43:59.319 --> 44:01.086
He prays for you daily.

44:01.087 --> 44:03.188
You are a knife in his heart.

44:05.859 --> 44:08.027
See the dogs spite the bear!

44:09.963 --> 44:12.031
I got... I got 6
on the brown dog.

44:12.032 --> 44:13.632
Who wants a piece of it?

44:20.407 --> 44:22.508
Winner takes the pot!

44:33.353 --> 44:35.521
What are they gonna
do with him?

44:36.556 --> 44:38.123
They're gonna fight him.

44:38.124 --> 44:40.359
Do they kill him?

44:40.360 --> 44:41.860
In the end, yeah.

44:41.861 --> 44:43.729
That's sad.

44:44.898 --> 44:46.465
Oh, not so much, not for him.

44:46.466 --> 44:49.435
He gets to die bravely,
fighting for what he longs for.

44:49.436 --> 44:50.669
What's that?

44:50.670 --> 44:52.037
Honor, really.

44:52.038 --> 44:53.739
And he gets to go
to bear heaven,

44:53.740 --> 44:56.342
wander around, eat as
much fish as he likes.

44:59.379 --> 45:01.680
Come with me.
I got a surprise for you.

45:12.525 --> 45:14.126
Up you climb, then.

45:14.127 --> 45:15.260
You really mean it?

45:15.261 --> 45:17.863
Go on, I'm right with you.

45:26.740 --> 45:28.007
That way.

45:30.877 --> 45:32.478
There you are.

45:32.479 --> 45:34.580
Don't get too close.

45:35.515 --> 45:37.116
I can see everywhere!

45:37.117 --> 45:39.351
I can see London.
And the ocean.

45:40.587 --> 45:42.588
I can see heaven!

45:43.790 --> 45:45.691
Hey, Jonathan...

45:45.692 --> 45:47.860
I mean, Brother Jonathan,
I'm sorry.

45:52.298 --> 45:54.600
There's something
I wanna tell you.

45:54.601 --> 45:56.902
I think I can see an angel.

45:56.903 --> 46:00.873
Listen to me. You know how
you and I are friends, yes?

46:00.874 --> 46:03.242
Well suppose I was to tell you

46:03.243 --> 46:05.110
we were something
closer than friends?

46:08.381 --> 46:10.315
And when Jack went away,

46:12.552 --> 46:15.254
for me that was sort of
like losing a son.

46:18.925 --> 46:20.492
But...

46:20.493 --> 46:22.194
What's that?

46:32.072 --> 46:33.338
Yah!

46:36.276 --> 46:40.512
Ellen, get inside the priory!
William Hamleigh's attacking!

46:41.981 --> 46:45.084
Get inside the priory!
William Hamleigh's attacking!

46:50.957 --> 46:52.558
We've got to get
away from here.

46:52.559 --> 46:54.059
I've got 6 pence on the...

46:54.060 --> 46:56.762
Never mind that now!
Get inside everyone!

47:05.872 --> 47:07.406
Run away!

47:26.526 --> 47:27.926
Everybody!

47:43.176 --> 47:44.676
No!

47:44.677 --> 47:45.778
Come, Aliena!

47:45.779 --> 47:47.246
We need to go.
I can't!

47:47.247 --> 47:48.213
No, it's all I have!

47:48.214 --> 47:49.181
Leave it, Aliena!

47:55.789 --> 47:57.322
Stay here.
Stay here, Aliena.

47:57.323 --> 47:59.391
Shut these doors.
These doors need shutting.

47:59.392 --> 48:00.459
You stay here!

48:00.460 --> 48:02.327
Stay!

48:15.875 --> 48:16.875
It's locked!

48:16.876 --> 48:18.010
Go to the cathedral.

48:18.011 --> 48:19.011
Follow me.

48:19.012 --> 48:20.479
Open the door!

48:23.683 --> 48:26.185
For the love
of God, let us in!

48:29.656 --> 48:31.557
Tell him
to get the keys!

48:36.462 --> 48:38.764
Remigius, what is it?
What's happening?

48:38.765 --> 48:41.834
Prior Philip,
there's a riot or something!

48:41.835 --> 48:43.502
Someone's attacking the fair!

48:43.503 --> 48:45.537
- Open! Let them in!
- Don't be a fool!

48:45.538 --> 48:47.840
Get out of my way! Out!

48:58.952 --> 49:01.220
Dear God!

49:01.221 --> 49:03.222
Dear God, why? Why?

49:04.290 --> 49:05.858
Let me through!
I can open it.

49:05.859 --> 49:06.859
It's locked!

49:06.860 --> 49:08.227
Ease back, let me through.

49:08.228 --> 49:10.863
Don't worry.
Don't worry, I can open it.

49:10.864 --> 49:13.031
Quickly, please.
Open it!

49:13.032 --> 49:14.967
Open it!

49:20.707 --> 49:22.641
Burn it! Come on!

49:31.484 --> 49:33.185
Burn everything.

49:36.122 --> 49:39.191
Burn the wool!
All of it!

49:45.265 --> 49:46.265
Aliena!

50:01.114 --> 50:03.715
Yah! Yah!

50:25.104 --> 50:26.471
Burn, witch.

50:28.474 --> 50:31.009
No! No! No!

50:31.010 --> 50:32.744
No! No!

50:35.548 --> 50:36.682
No!

50:40.486 --> 50:41.486
Aaah!

51:14.988 --> 51:16.088
Yah!

51:30.803 --> 51:32.170
Tom!

51:33.539 --> 51:35.079
Tom!

51:37.175 --> 51:38.576
Don't meddle, monk!

51:43.165 --> 51:44.916
It was all for nothing,
Tom Builder.

52:14.766 --> 52:16.715
Yah! Yah!

